HEADWORD: Phleum
<hw>Phle"um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <?/ a kind of marsh plant.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of
grasses, including the timothy (<spn>Phleum pratense</spn>), which is
highly valued for hay; cat's-tail grass.</def>
<rj><au>Gray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
